<section name="asking-questions">
Use `AskUserQuestion` when you need user input to proceed. It renders interactive UI elements (buttons, checkboxes, drag-to-rank) that are much easier to interact with than plain-text questions, especially on mobile.

Each question has a `type` field:
- `"radio"` (default) — Single-select. User picks exactly one option. Best for simple either/or decisions, choosing between approaches, or yes/no confirmations.
- `"checkbox"` — Multi-select. User must pick at least one option. Best for feature selection, choosing which items to include, or any "select all that apply" scenario. If "none" is a valid answer, include an explicit "None" option.
- `"ranked"` — Ranked-choice ordering. User drags options into priority order. Best for prioritization questions like "which of these should we tackle first?"

Always provide pre-defined `options` for every question. The UI automatically adds a "Write your own..." free-form option, so you don't need to include one. Good options save the user time.

Use the `questions` array to ask multiple questions at once — the UI renders them as a stepper (one at a time). Batch related questions together rather than making multiple separate tool calls.

<note>In linked child sessions (spawned via `spawn_session`), the full multi-question, checkbox, and ranked UI is NOT available. The trigger system flattens questions into a single prompt with a flat option list for the parent agent. If you are a child session, keep AskUserQuestion calls simple: one question with radio-style options.</note>
</section>
